sample_comments.negatives:
Staff is not speaking English, so it complicates all communication;
I booked sea view room and garden view room with king-size bed, as a result I got 2 similar rooms with similar view - staff at reception was not understanding (or didn't want to change);
There was constant problem with hot water, and only on 3rd day in the evening it was solved, when next morning we were leaving;
Waiters in restaurant didn't understand any questions or requests, restaurant was usually empty, but we were waiting for food 40+ minutes;
Kids club is closed at 6 pm, basically when the time in the pool is also over - what to do with kids in the evening?
Kids club by size was smaller than regular room, while main audience which is coming are parents with kids;
There is nothing else to do for kids, while the territory is very big. Is it difficult to create a playground instead of having all those gardens which are not used by anyone?
